  "narrative": "DRIVER\nUSD leads D1 CSM at 100 but is fading hard on H4 at 44, a 56-point divergence that is the most important short-term signal in this brief, while CHF accelerates to H4 CSM 100 versus D1 33 and AUD surges to H4 CSM 70 versus D1 31, both flagged as critical divergences confirming real-money rotation out of USD and into safe-haven CHF and risk-proxy AUD simultaneously within a Risk-Off High regime. USDCHF short captures the CHF acceleration directly with EURUSD correlation at -0.88 reinforcing the move, while AUDUSD and AUDJPY long express AUD strength with NZDUSD at +0.90 and NZDJPY at +0.92 amplifying the cluster. USDCAD D1 and H4 both print Strong Buy at +5, overriding the USD fade narrative on that specific pair given CAD sits weakest at CSM 18.\n\nMOMENTUM\nGaining: None\nFading: None\n\nWATCH\nUSDCAD technical breakout confirmation on H4 triggers continued CAD selling toward 1.3900 given D1 and H4 aligned Strong Buy.\nUS 10Y yield further compression below 4.50 hits USDJPY long thesis and validates AUDJPY upside continuation.\nCopper sustaining above 6.30 accelerates AUDUSD toward H4 resistance and pulls NZDUSD higher through the 0.90 correlation channel.",
